#compdef jco
# ============================================================================
# jco - JavaScript toolchain for WebAssembly
#        Components (TypeScript/Node,
#        Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception)
#
# Author : Guy Bedford + Victor Adossi
#           (Bytecode Alliance; Guy Bedford
#           formerly at Mozilla on the
#           SpiderMonkey + WASI teams;
#           Victor Adossi at Cosmonic)
# Upstream: https://github.com/bytecodealliance/jco
# npm pkg : @bytecodealliance/jco
#
# `jco` is the JavaScript toolchain for the
# WebAssembly Component Model - the modern
# language-agnostic WASM composition layer
# that allows components written in
# different languages (Rust + JavaScript +
# Python + C + Go + ...) to interoperate
# through WIT (WebAssembly Interface Type)
# definitions.
#
# Key capabilities:
#   1. **Transpile**: convert WASM
#      Components to runnable JavaScript
#      + core Wasm (for browser + Node +
#      Deno + Bun execution)
#   2. **Componentize**: compile JavaScript
#      source into a WASM Component using
#      Bedford's StarlingMonkey (the
#      Component-Model-friendly JavaScript
#      engine; descendant of SpiderMonkey)
#   3. **Run**: execute WASI Command
#      components locally
#   4. **Serve**: serve WASI HTTP
#      components as local HTTP servers
#   5. **Optimize**: invoke wasm-opt on
#      components for size + speed
#   6. **WIT extraction**: extract WIT
#      type definitions from existing
#      components
#   7. **WAT printing**: convert binary
#      WASM modules to WebAssembly Text
#      Format for inspection
#
# Architecture:
#   - **WIT bindings**: WebAssembly
#     Interface Types define the
#     language-agnostic component API
#     surface; jco generates JavaScript
#     bindings + TypeScript .d.ts types
#     from WIT
#   - **Component Model**: WASM
#     Components compose lower-level
#     WASM modules into higher-level
#     applications with cross-language
#     interop
#   - **Preview 1 vs Preview 2**: jco
#     supports both WASI snapshot
#     generations; Preview 2 is the
#     current focus with the Component
#     Model being canonical going
#     forward
#   - **StarlingMonkey**: the WASM-
#     packaged JavaScript engine that
#     jco componentize uses; built on
#     SpiderMonkey + the WASM Component
#     Model integration
#
# Distinguishing features vs alternatives:
#   - **Canonical Component Model
#     toolchain** (Bytecode Alliance's
#     official JS tooling; same
#     organization that maintains
#     wasmtime + Cranelift + WASI spec)
#   - **TypeScript-first** (generates
#     full .d.ts types from WIT;
#     idiomatic TypeScript API surface)
#   - **Multi-target output** (browser +
#     Node + Deno + Cloudflare Workers
#     + standalone WASI runtimes)
#   - **AOT compilation via Weval**
#     (componentize --aot uses Weval -
#     a partial evaluator for WASM -
#     to pre-execute JavaScript at
#     compile time for faster startup)
#   - **WASI HTTP serving** (jco serve
#     runs WASI HTTP components as
#     real local HTTP servers for
#     development + testing)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Compile JavaScript to portable WASM
#     Components for cross-language
#     deployment
#   - Generate TypeScript bindings for
#     Rust/Go/Python WASM Components to
#     consume in Node/browser
#     applications
#   - Serve WASI HTTP components locally
#     for development (jco serve)
#   - Optimize WASM Components for
#     production deployment (jco opt)
#   - Inspect WASM Component metadata +
#     interface types (jco wit +
#     metadata-show)
#   - Local execution of WASI Command
#     components (jco run)
#
# Usage:
#   jco <command> [options]
#
# Subcommands (commander.js):
#   componentize <js-source>       - compile
#                                     a
#                                     JavaScript
#                                     module
#                                     into a
#                                     WASM
#                                     Component
#                                     using
#                                     Starling
#                                     Monkey
#   transpile <wasm-component>     - transpile
#                                     a WASM
#                                     Component
#                                     to JS +
#                                     core
#                                     Wasm
#                                     for
#                                     browser
#                                     /Node
#                                     execution
#   types <wit-path>               - generate
#                                     TypeScript
#                                     .d.ts +
#                                     JavaScript
#                                     bindings
#                                     from
#                                     WIT
#   guest-types <wit-path>         - (experimental)
#                                     generate
#                                     guest-
#                                     side
#                                     types
#                                     for the
#                                     given
#                                     WIT
#   run <wasm-component>           - run a
#                                     WASI
#                                     Command
#                                     component
#                                     locally
#   serve <wasm-component>         - serve
#                                     a WASI
#                                     HTTP
#                                     component
#                                     as a
#                                     local
#                                     HTTP
#                                     server
#   opt <wasm-component>           - optimize
#                                     a WASM
#                                     Component
#                                     using
#                                     wasm-
#                                     opt
#   wit <wasm-component>           - extract
#                                     WIT
#                                     type
#                                     definitions
#                                     from a
#                                     WASM
#                                     Component
#   print <wasm-file>              - print
#                                     the
#                                     WebAssembly
#                                     WAT
#                                     text
#                                     for a
#                                     binary
#                                     file
#   metadata-show <wasm-file>      - extract
#                                     producer
#                                     metadata
#                                     for a
#                                     WASM
#                                     binary
#   metadata-add <wasm-file>       - add
#                                     producer
#                                     metadata
#                                     for a
#                                     WASM
#                                     binary
#   parse <wat-file>               - parse
#                                     the
#                                     Wasm
#                                     text
#                                     format
#                                     into a
#                                     binary
#                                     file
#   new <wasm-module>              - create
#                                     a
#                                     Component
#                                     adapted
#                                     from a
#                                     core
#                                     Wasm
#                                     module
#   embed <wit> <wasm-module>      - embed
#                                     the
#                                     component
#                                     typing
#                                     section
#                                     into a
#                                     core
#                                     Wasm
#                                     module
#   help [command]                 - display
#                                     help
#                                     for
#                                     command
#
# `transpile` flags:
#       --name <name>              - custom
#                                     output
#                                     name
#   -o, --out-dir <dir>            - output
#                                     directory
#   -m, --minify                   - minify
#                                     the JS
#                                     output
#   -O, --optimize                 - optimize
#                                     the
#                                     component
#                                     first
#       --no-typescript            - do not
#                                     output
#                                     TypeScript
#                                     .d.ts
#                                     types
#       --valid-lifting-optimization - optimize
#                                     binary
#                                     validations
#       --import-bindings <mode>   - bindings
#                                     mode
#                                     for
#                                     imports
#                                     (js +
#                                     optimized
#                                     + hybrid
#                                     + direct-
#                                     optimized)
#       --async-mode <mode>        - use
#                                     async
#                                     imports/
#                                     exports
#                                     (sync +
#                                     jspi)
#       --async-wasi-imports       - async
#                                     component
#                                     imports
#                                     from
#                                     WASI
#                                     interfaces
#       --async-wasi-exports       - async
#                                     component
#                                     exports
#                                     from
#                                     WASI
#                                     interfaces
#       --async-imports <list>     - async
#                                     component
#                                     imports
#                                     (repeatable)
#       --async-exports <list>     - async
#                                     component
#                                     exports
#                                     (repeatable)
#       --tracing                  - emit
#                                     tracing
#                                     calls
#                                     on
#                                     function
#                                     entry/
#                                     exit
#   -b, --base64-cutoff <bytes>    - inline
#                                     core
#                                     Wasm
#                                     under
#                                     this
#                                     byte
#                                     size as
#                                     base64
#       --tla-compat               - enable
#                                     compatibility
#                                     for
#                                     environments
#                                     without
#                                     top-
#                                     level
#                                     await
#       --no-nodejs-compat         - disable
#                                     Node.js
#                                     compatibility
#                                     without
#                                     a fetch
#                                     global
#   -M, --map <spec=path>          - custom
#                                     import
#                                     mappings
#                                     (specifier=
#                                     ./output)
#       --no-wasi-shim             - disable
#                                     automatic
#                                     WASI
#                                     import
#                                     rewriting
#       --stub                     - generate
#                                     a stub
#                                     implementation
#                                     from a
#                                     WIT
#                                     file
#       --js                       - output
#                                     JS
#                                     instead
#                                     of
#                                     core
#                                     WebAssembly
#   -I, --instantiation <mode>     - output
#                                     for
#                                     custom
#                                     module
#                                     instantiation
#                                     (async
#                                     + sync)
#   -q, --quiet                    - disable
#                                     output
#                                     summary
#       --no-namespaced-exports    - disable
#                                     namespaced
#                                     exports
#                                     for
#                                     typescript
#
# `componentize` flags:
#   -w, --wit <path>               - WIT path
#                                     to build
#                                     with
#   -n, --world-name <name>        - WIT
#                                     world
#                                     to build
#       --aot                      - enable
#                                     Weval
#                                     AOT
#                                     compilation
#                                     of JS
#       --aot-min-stack-size-bytes <n> - min
#                                     stack
#                                     size
#                                     used
#                                     during
#                                     AOT
#       --weval-bin <path>         - custom
#                                     weval
#                                     binary
#   -d, --disable <feature>        - disable
#                                     WASI
#                                     features
#                                     (clocks
#                                     + http
#                                     + random
#                                     + stdio
#                                     + fetch-
#                                     event
#                                     + all)
#       --enable <feature>         - enable
#                                     WASI
#                                     features
#       --debug                    - configure
#                                     jco for
#                                     debug
#       --preview2-adapter <path>  - custom
#                                     preview2
#                                     adapter
#                                     path
#       --engine <path>            - use a
#                                     specific
#                                     Starling
#                                     Monkey
#                                     build
#   -o, --out <file>               - output
#                                     component
#                                     file
#
# Standard:
#   -h, --help                     - show
#                                     help
#   -V, --version                  - output
#                                     version
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Compile JavaScript to a WASM Component
#   jco componentize my-component.js \
#     --wit world.wit \
#     --world-name my-world \
#     -o my-component.wasm
#
#   # Transpile WASM Component to JS for
#   # Node execution
#   jco transpile my-component.wasm \
#     --out-dir dist/
#
#   # Generate TypeScript types from WIT
#   jco types world.wit --out-dir types/
#
#   # Run a WASI Command component locally
#   jco run my-cli.wasm
#
#   # Serve a WASI HTTP component on
#   # http://localhost:8080
#   jco serve my-http-component.wasm
#
#   # Optimize a Component
#   jco opt my-component.wasm -o optimized.wasm
#
#   # Inspect a Component's WIT interface
#   jco wit my-component.wasm
#
#   # AOT-compile JS for faster startup
#   jco componentize my-component.js \
#     --wit world.wit \
#     --world-name my-world \
#     --aot \
#     -o my-component-aot.wasm
#
#   # Minify + optimize for browser
#   # deployment
#   jco transpile my-component.wasm \
#     --minify --optimize \
#     --out-dir dist/
#
#   # Convert WAT text to binary WASM
#   jco parse my-module.wat -o my-module.wasm
#
#   # Print WAT for inspection
#   jco print my-component.wasm
#
# The wasmtime ecosystem lane (server-side
# WASM runtime) is implicit here - jco is
# the Bytecode Alliance's *JavaScript-side*
# tooling that pairs with their Rust-side
# wasmtime runtime. The full BC Alliance
# stack:
#   - **wasmtime** (Rust runtime; Axis 286
#     Rust opener at R1556 via _wasi-vfs)
#   - **Cranelift** (Rust JIT compiler
#     backend)
#   - **WASI spec** (the WebAssembly System
