#   - **Mozilla SpiderMonkey team
#     contributions** (engine
#     integration for WASM modules)
#
# Bedford's role across the Node + WASM
# ecosystem is *module system + runtime
# integration infrastructure*. His work
# on jco reflects continuity from his
# es-module-shims + SystemJS work -
# providing JavaScript-side tooling that
# bridges different module formats +
# execution contexts. The Component
# Model is the latest evolution of this
# multi-format module-interop problem
# space.
#
# Victor Adossi (Cosmonic) brings
# Cosmonic's commercial WASM Component
# Model expertise. Cosmonic is one of
# the major commercial Bytecode Alliance
# members + a major contributor to
# wasmCloud (the WASM-based service
# mesh).
#
# Bedford + Adossi + Bytecode Alliance
# joining the canonical-Node cohort at
# the *spec-author canonical
# implementation* level is the third
# spec-author-canonical-implementer
# pairing documented for Axis 286 (Rust
# wasmtime + Node jco both from
# Bytecode Alliance). This is
# structurally distinctive - very few
# axes have spec-author canonical
# implementations across MULTIPLE
# lanes from the same organization.
#
# Cross-language spec authorship pattern
# for Axis 286:
#   - WASM/WASI spec: Bytecode Alliance
#   - Rust canonical: Bytecode Alliance
#     wasmtime (spec-author canonical)
#   - Go canonical: Tetrate wazero
#     (third-party implementation)
#   - Node canonical: Bytecode Alliance
#     jco (spec-author canonical)
#
# Bytecode Alliance's dual spec-author
# canonical presence across Rust + Node
# is unique in the corpus - matched only
# by Google's Protocol Buffers presence
# in Go (Axis 279) + (transitive)
# spec-author canonical role in Rust via
# tonic/prost. The Bytecode Alliance
# pattern is even more pronounced: the
# alliance authors the WASM/WASI specs
# AND maintains canonical libraries in
# multiple language lanes simultaneously.
#
# jco uses the Bytecode Alliance's full
# stack for:
#   - WIT parsing + binding generation
#     (via wit-bindgen-equivalent JS
#     code generation)
#   - WASM Component Model
#     instantiation (Preview 1 + Preview
#     2 + Component Model)
#   - StarlingMonkey integration (for
#     componentize JavaScript-to-WASM
#     compilation)
#   - WASM optimization (wraps wasm-
#     opt from binaryen)
#
# This is the canonical use case for
# jco in production Node + browser
# applications: bridge between
# JavaScript/TypeScript codebases and
# the WASM Component Model ecosystem
# (compile JS to components + consume
# components written in other
# languages from JS).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 286 :: WebAssembly runtime + tooling
#              libraries
#              (WebAssembly spec
#              compliant runtimes + WASI
#              implementations + JIT/AOT
#              compilation + component
#              model + WASM tooling)
# Round 1558 :: TS/Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 286
#
# Cross-language canonical library family
# for this axis (closed):
#   Rust    : bytecodealliance/wasmtime  [R1556 _wasi-vfs]
#             (Bytecode Alliance;
#              canonical Rust WASM
#              runtime; Cranelift JIT;
#              spec-author canonical)
